description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meavy Assessment Ward – Band 5 Staff Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust is looking for passionate and experienced nurses to join our Meavy Assessment Ward as Band 5 Staff Nurses, where we are currently deliverying our COVID-19 pathway and we are looking at developing the area into a 12-bedded isolation Ward for patients with transmitable diseases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meavy Assessment Ward is a thriving service where we aim to deliver prompt initial medical and nursing assessment and elaborate early treatment and care plans; this is all delivered thanks to the efforts of a fantastic multidisciplinary clinical team and specifically the excellent nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidates will have experience in the acute setting, ideally within acute medicine, general surgery and urgent care; infectious diseases experience will be an asset. As a Band 5 Staff Nurse, you will deliver outstanding patient care and show excellent nursing assessment skills to maintain the admission, discharge and transfer of patients through Meavy Ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we will support you with an innovative and individualized programme of on-going professional and career development clinical perspective – to  be able to care for acuitely unwell patients (Level 1 patients) as well as doing in-depth nursing asessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information about this opportunity or to arrange an informal visit, please contact via e-mail:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stacey Coxon,  Ward Manager for Meavy Ward s.coxon@nhs.net or Cecilia Vezzani, Deputy Ward Manager c.vezzani@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to be held on the week commencing on the 16th of November of 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
